al dialogue with the learner as a being engaged in the psychical work of making, and re-making, an identity. Viewed in its entirety, this study takes the form of a kind of triangulation of three elements: the linguistically described phenomenon of the silent period; the psychoanalytically oriented problem of the making of the self; and the real and remembered experiences of individuals who live in the silent space between languages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPsychoanalysis. 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aSilence. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aL2 self.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aforeign language learning.  asecond language learning.  asilence.  asilent period.1 aRiley, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102473808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106067130 cprintz978185359698840uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978185359699540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781853596995423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781853596995/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102473-8  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aP